<plot>Desperate to escape a self-destructive existence, Wesley (Jay Sullivan) takes an experimental anti-depressant called Elotane. When the medication produces adverse side effects, Harold (Tom Sawyer), Wesley's ex-coworker, seems to be the only one who can reach him. He sympathizes with his ordeal, yet is motivated for entirely different reasons. Ultimately, Harold must decide whether to assist or destroy Wesley's path to alleviation. Mend is a psychological drama exploring a man's struggle to transcend suicide and forbidden love.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?365732</url></doc>
